			<div class="post-4074 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-russia-2 tag-gazprom">

				<div class="entry">

					<h2><a href="http://blog.mktgeist.com/2012/06/30/gazprom-to-boost-export-to-eu-by-50-rt/">Gazprom to boost export to EU by 50%&nbsp;[RT]</a></h2>

					<div class="post-info">
						<p>
							<span class="time">June 30, 2012</span>
															<span class="author">by <a href="http://blog.mktgeist.com/author/mktgeistmike/" title="Posts by mktgeistmike" rel="author">mktgeistmike</a></span>
																						<span class="post-comments"><a href="http://blog.mktgeist.com/2012/06/30/gazprom-to-boost-export-to-eu-by-50-rt/#respond" title="Comment on Gazprom to boost export to EU by 50%&nbsp;[RT]">Leave a comment</a></span>
																				</p>
					</div>

					<p>Russia plans to boost gas exports to Europe by up to 230 billion cubic meters (bcm) by 2030 from the current 150 billion, the Russian Ministry of Energy has announced.</p>
<p>Gas production in Russia is expected to increase by 30-50% by 2030, while consumption is expected to grow by only 20-30%, according to the Ministry. They say it would create opportunities to boost exports. Currently the country produces 670 bcm per year.</p>
<p>At the end of the month Gazprom reported increase in production and supply to the local market in the first quarter. The production was up to 141.8 bcm and the supply grew by 3.5 bcm to 104.6 bcm.</p>
<p><a href="http://rt.com/business/news/gazprom-eu-export-plans-213/">Read more</a></p>
<div class="clear"></div>

				</div>

				<div class="post-meta">
